From 3852b885ed02bc6bdfc6b142e6bd09a6fd168039 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 12:58:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add ChainAPI precompiled with vendor HE bridge and adjust
 dependency build flags

### Motivation
- Provide a ChainAPI precompiled contract backed by a vendor HE (homomorphic encryption) shared object bridge to expose vendor crypto functions inside precompiled contracts.
- Ensure third-party dependencies (CryptoPP and RocksDB) are built with controlled C/C++ standards and PIC/threading flags for better portability and to allow static linkage into shared contexts.
- Expose a new precompiled address for ChainAPI and wire it into the precompiled registration process.

### Description
- Added a vendor bridge `CallVendorHE` (`CallVendorHE.h/.cpp`) that loads a vendor SO with `dlopen` and exposes typed wrapper methods for encryption, arithmetic, substring/length ops and lifecycle operations.
- Implemented `ChainAPIPrecompiled` (`ChainAPIPrecompiled.h/.cpp`) which maps ABI calls to the vendor bridge and returns ABI-encoded results and mapped error codes.
- Introduced a new precompiled address constant `CHAIN_API_ADDRESS` in `libprecompiled/Common.h` and registered `ChainAPIPrecompiled` in `UserPrecompiled.h` template to enable the contract at runtime.
- Updated `libprecompiled/CMakeLists.txt` to link `precompiled` with `${CMAKE_DL_LIBS}` and added the new `extension` sources under `libprecompiled/extension`.
- Adjusted build flags for vendored dependencies: in `cmake/ProjectCryptopp.cmake` and `cmake/ProjectRocksDB.cmake` set explicit C/C++ standards (`C++11`, `C99`), required settings, and refined `CMAKE_C_FLAGS`/`CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS` to include `-fPIC`, `-pthread` and disable compiler extensions where appropriate.

### Testing
- Ran a full CMake configure and build (`cmake` + `cmake --build`) of the project with the updated build scripts and the `precompiled` target which completed successfully.
- Built the static dependency artifacts (cryptopp, rocksdb) through the external project builds and confirmed the expected byproducts (`libcryptopp.a`, `librocksdb.a`) were produced.
- Executed the available automated test target (`ctest` / `make test`) after the build and observed no failing tests.
